<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In JSON, the presence of invalid Unicode should produce an error. In the case of PHP's ext/json it instead returns NULL (presumably to avoid unnecessary errors). Zend_Json_Encoder, the PHP native implementation used either by choice or in the absence of ext/json does neither, instead pulling out what appears to be a codepoint reference. This gives rise to invalid JSON strings in that such refs are lost and presented as literal characters.</p>

<p>Reproduce with:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>require_once 'Zend/Json/Encoder.php';
 
$source = &lt;&lt;</code></pre>

<p>Expected (as per ext/json):</p>

<p>NULL</p>

<p>Actual:</p>

<p>"ab\u005c0022"</p>

